<Docs title="Command" description="Phase handlers as dispatchable commands." eyebrow="Pattern">
  <p><strong>Where:</strong> <code>src/flow/phases/*.ts</code>.</p>
  <p>
    <strong>The rule:</strong> each phase is a self-contained unit with <code>enter</code>,
    <code>skip</code>, <code>exit</code>. They're commands: you dispatch one, it runs,
    transitions to the next.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Why:</strong> phases are testable in isolation. You can also log/record phase
    transitions for replay or telemetry.
  </p>
</Docs>
